<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Stablecoins</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/24841104.252088/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDgtMTEvY3J5cHRvLWhhY2tlcnMtYXJlLW5pY2Utbm93/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa53491ce" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;"> talked a couple of weeks ago</a> about a core proble=
m for stablecoin issuers:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding=
-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">(Many) p=
eople who buy stablecoins would like each stablecoin to be backed by exactl=
y $1 in a bank account.[1]</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Banks o=
ften don=E2=80=99t want to hold deposits from crypto companies (like stable=
coin issuers), and these days they don=E2=80=99t want to hold deposits gene=
rally, meaning that they might decline your deposits or pay you negative in=
terest.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Also it is not really best=
 practices to put all your cash in one bank account.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">So you buy commercial paper and stuff, and your money is=
 not all in a bank account.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">And th=
en you go around saying =E2=80=9Cyour stablecoins are 100% backed by U.S. d=
ollars in a bank account,=E2=80=9D because that=E2=80=99s what people want =
to hear, but you=E2=80=99re lying.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=
=E2=80=99s not ideal. The consortium behind USDC, a $27 billion stablecoin,=
 did this, and regretted it, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/24841104.252088/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDgtMjMvY29pbmJhc2UtY2lyY2xlLXRvLW1vdmUtYWxsLXVzZGMtcmVzZXJ=
2ZXMtaW50by1jYXNoLXRyZWFzdXJpZXM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBca085dc0" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> has now</a> =E2=
=80=9Csaid all the reserves of the second-largest cryptocurrency stable coi=
n will shift into cash and short-term U.S. Treasuries, forgoing riskier inv=
estments.=E2=80=9D Fine. I=E2=80=99m not sure that=E2=80=99s a good investm=
ent policy, but I guess it=E2=80=99s a good public-relations policy, so fin=
e.[2]=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know what =E2=
=80=9Ccash=E2=80=9D means in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/24841104.252088/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2VudHJlLmlvL2Jsb2cvdXNkYy1yZXNl=
cnZlcy1jb21wb3NpdGlvbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcae93f4a" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the USDC announcement</a>. =
They=E2=80=99ll hold =E2=80=9Ccash and short duration US Treasuries.=E2=80=
=9D Presumably that does not mean =E2=80=9Ca drawer full of $100 bills.=E2=
=80=9D Presumably it means bank accounts, perhaps other things.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You know what <em>would</em> be ideal? A stablecoin th=
at was a pure wrapper for a digital dollar. Right now you can=E2=80=99t get=
 a =E2=80=9Cdigital dollar,=E2=80=9D in the sense of =E2=80=9Ca thing that =
is worth a dollar in any imaginable state of the world,=E2=80=9D though you=
 can come very close. (An FDIC insured bank account is pretty much a digita=
l dollar; you=E2=80=99d have to work pretty hard to come up with a scenario=
 in which you lose access to=C2=A0that dollar even briefly. But FDIC insura=
nce limits are considerably lower than $27=C2=A0billion.)</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">But=C2=A0<em>some=C2=A0</em>people can get pure uncut digita=
